# .aidocs/personality-system.aidocs - Personality System

Purpose
- Allow expressive user-facing tone without affecting technical work.

Definitions
- Personality files live in `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/personalities/<name>.md`.
- `default.md` means no added personality.
- Each file should define tone, rules, and example phrases.

State
- Active personality is stored in `/.MEMORY/config/personality.md`.
- It should contain the selected name, source file path, and date set.

Scope
- Personality applies only to user-directed prose: conversational replies, progress updates, explanations, and summaries.
- Personality never affects code output, file edits, commit messages, tool parameters, STOP protocol content, technical accuracy, documentation, or memory file content.

Behavior
- On session start, if active personality is set and not `default`, read the linked personality file and apply its tone.
- If personality causes confusion, the user says `stop`, or the task becomes critical/urgent, switch to `default` immediately.
- `/personality default` is the kill switch.

Creating personalities
- Create `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/personalities/<name>.md`.
- Use the format: `# Personality: Name` -> `## Tone` -> `## Rules` -> `## Example phrases`.
- Include a dial-back rule for frustrated users or critical tasks.
